<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>About</title>

  <style>
    /* Sticky‑note background */
    body {
      font-family: "Bradley Hand", cursive;
      background: #ffeeb0;
      color: #1a4b8c;
      padding: 2rem;
      line-height: 1.6;
      max-width: 650px;
      margin: 0 auto;
    }

    /* Sticky‑note header */
    h1 {
      font-size: 2rem;
      letter-spacing: 1px;
      background: #ffeeb0;
      border: 1px solid #d8cfa0;
      box-shadow: 3px 4px 7px rgba(0,0,0,0.2);
      color: #1a4b8c;
      padding: 0.7rem 1.2rem;
      width: fit-content;
      transform: rotate(-2deg);
      margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
      position: relative;
      z-index: 2;
    }

    p {
      margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
      position: relative;
      z-index: 2;
    }

    /* Sticky‑note link back to Seasonal Notes */
    .back-link {
      --tilt: 2deg;
      display: inline-block;
      background: #ffeeb0;
      border: 1px solid #d8cfa0;
      box-shadow: 3px 4px 7px rgba(0,0,0,0.2);
      padding: 0.7rem 1.2rem;
      transform: rotate(var(--tilt));
      font-family: "Bradley Hand", cursive;
      text-decoration: none;
      color: #1a4b8c;
      margin-top: 2rem;
      position: fixed;
      bottom: 1.5rem;
      left: 1.5rem;
      z-index: 10;
    }

    /* Mobile fix: prevent overlap but keep tilt */
    @media (max-width: 700px) {
      .back-link {
        position: static;
        display: block;
        margin: 2rem auto 0 auto;
        transform: rotate(2deg); /* tilt restored */
        text-align: center;
      }
    }
  </style>
</head>

<body>

  <h1>About</h1>

  <p>
    Seasonal Notes is a small, quiet experiment in noticing. Instead of building a traditional website with tidy pages and rigid structure, this project gathers fragments – small seasonal impressions – and scatters them across a single canvas.
  </p>

  <p>
    The notes are intentionally a little crooked, like sticky notes pinned to a wall or scribbles left on a desk. They are not meant to stand alone as pages. They belong together, side by side, forming a loose collage of the year.
  </p>

  <p>
    This page exists only to explain the intention behind the form – a companion note to the main piece, written in the margin.
  </p>

  <a class="back-link" href="../">Seasonal Notes</a>

</body>
</html>
